 href=\"https://twitter.com/fluttercm\">Flutter Cameroon</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T21:36:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Solido/awesome-flutter","categoryHTML":"<h2>Community</h2><h3>cm Cameroon</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>Telegram <a href=\"https://t.me/fluttercameroon\">Flutter &#x26; Dart Community CM</a></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T21:36:57.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"playcanvas/awesome-playcanvas","categoryHTML":"<h2>Browser Games</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://poki.com/en/g/stickman-climb\">Stickman Climb</a> - Physics based puzzle game.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T21:27:18.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h3>PHP</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://phpwomen.org/\">PHPWomen</a></p>\n<p>An inclusive, global user-group providing a support network within the PHP community.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Chatrooms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://anitab.org/systers/\">Systers</a></p>\n<p>A community of Anita Borg Institute members. It provides a space to discuss and contribute towards Open Source projects, participate in events and discuss any aspect of technology.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Chatrooms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://witchat.github.io/\">Women in Tech</a></p>\n<p>A safe, confidential space for women who work in technology to chat and support each other.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.aspirations.org/aspireit\">AspireIT</a></p>\n<p>AspireIT is a National Center for Women and Information Technology education program and network for K-12 girls. The program connects nearly 700 programming and computer science organizations in schools in 45 US states, DC, the US Virgin Islands and Puerto Rico. AspireIT also offers student awards and local program development support for educators.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.awis.org/\">Association for Women in Science</a></p>\n<p>AWIS is a global network that inspires bold leadership, research, and solutions that advance women in STEM, spark innovation, promote organizational success and drive systemic change. In addition to their networking and career growth support they publish a magazine, offer scholarships and grants, and host events.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.builtbygirls.com/\">Built by Girls</a></p>\n<p>Built by Girls is an early career community supporting women and non-binary tech professionals. The group maintains a calendar of workshops, panels, office tours and networking events. The WAVE mentorship program matches participants with a different industry professional as an advisor every three months.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.meetup.com/Chicago-WomenTech/\">Chicago WomenTech</a></p>\n<p>Chicago WomenTech is a Meetup group with over 4500 members for women in tech to collaborate and network in the Chicago area.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://codegirls.de/\">Code Girls</a> - <em>Loc:</em> <img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/ba/Flag_of_Germany.svg\" alt=\"Germany\" width=\"30\"> - <em>Lang: Deutsch Only</em></p>\n<p>An enthusiastic group of ladies with a focus on web-technologies who want to learn to code, need support in coding, or simply want to understand how the web is made. They meet regularly every two weeks. Everyone is welcome.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.codess.net/\">Codess</a></p>\n<p>Codess is an international community for female coders initiated by Microsoft. Codess was established to explore ways to promote gender diversity in the engineering field. They offer networking events and mentorship opportunities for women in tech.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.lambdaladies.com/\">Lambda Ladies</a></p>\n<p>Lambda Ladies is an online community for anyone who identifies as a girl or woman and is interested in functional programming. Complete beginners are welcome.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://community.oracle.com/groups/otn-women-in-technology/overview\">Oracle Women in Technology</a></p>\n<p>Oracle WIT Community Group - a place to share experiences and mentor women in high tech roles. They share knowledge and technical resources and engage with other women throughout the Oracle technical community.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.meetup.com/SanFranciscoWomenandDiversityInTech/\">San Francisco Women in Tech</a></p>\n<p>San Francisco Women in Tech is a Meetup group with over 3200 members for women in San Francisco and Silicon Valley to network and learn about new technologies and opportunities in a context that values diversity in the industry.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Communities/Groups</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.womenhackfornonprofits.com/\">Women Hack For Non-Profits (WHFNP)</a></p>\n<p>Women Hack for Non-Profits (WHFNP) is a volunteer community that enhances the skills of women in technology, supports their development and provides opportunities to explore open source. The group matches skilled women to open source projects that are being developed for non-profits, charities and individuals to create a positive social impact.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Hackerspace/Makerspace</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.programaria.org/\">Maria Lab</a> - <em>Loc:</em> <img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg\" alt=\"United States\" width=\"30\"></p>\n<p>It is a hackerspace/makerspace and is focused to teach and spread and technology with women's empowerment in a safety environment. Maria Lab promote diversity and union of the womens.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Hackerspace/Makerspace</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://mothership.hackermoms.org/\">Mothership HackerMoms</a> - <em>Loc:</em> <img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg\" alt=\"United States\" width=\"30\"></p>\n<p>It was the first all-women hackerspace, this space is located in Berkeley and have the goal to explore the culture hacker/maker and learn about entrepreneurship, design, DIY crafts all of that in hands-on workshops. Those workshops could be towards for moms of every gender or for the kids.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Linux/OpenSource</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.debian.org/women/\">Debian Women</a></p>\n<p>The Debian Women project was founded in May 2004. We seek to balance and diversify the Debian Project by actively engaging with interested women and encouraging them to become more involved with Debian.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Linux/OpenSource</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Women\">Fedora Women</a></p>\n<p>Fedora Women is a project designed to connect and assist women who are interested in using and contributing to Fedora.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Linux/OpenSource</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://community.kde.org/KDE_Women\">KDE Women</a></p>\n<p>KDE Women is a group of women in the KDE community. We are here to help increase the number of women in Open Source and to support each other.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Linux/OpenSource</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/LinuxChix\">Linux Chix</a></p>\n<p>It is a women-oriented Linux community. It is designed to provide both technical and social support for women Linux users, although men are encouraged to help and contribute.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Linux/OpenSource</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://wiki.ubuntu-women.org/\">Ubuntu Women</a></p>\n<p>The Ubuntu Women Project was founded in 2006 and aims to foster Women contributors and community involvement through mentoring and inspiration. The Ubuntu Women Team has many projects with which we attempt to boost the visibility of women within all areas of Ubuntu, and we invite you to help out.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Speakers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.callbackwomen.com/\">CallbackWomen</a></p>\n<p>The mission of CallbackWomen is to radically expand gender diversity at the podium of professional programmers' conferences. Call for proposals (CFPs) are shared via Twitter: <a href=\"https://twitter.com/callbackwomen\">https://twitter.com/callbackwomen</a>.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Speakers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"http://insideoutproject.xyz/mulheres-palestrantes/\">Mulheres Palestrantes</a> - <em>Loc:</em> <img src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/0/05/Flag_of_Brazil.svg\" alt=\"Brazil\" width=\"30\"> - <em>Lang: PT-BR only</em></p>\n<p>Given the still small number of women speaking at events (especially technology) here in Brazil, a spreadsheet was created to give these women visibility and to encourage others to start.\nMulheres Palestrantes is a project that keeps a list of women who talk about themes related to programming, design, entrepreneurship and technology in general, this project was born from trying to organize the data of the worksheet in a more visual, facilitating access, reducing duplication and facilitating research.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:52:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"awesome-selfhosted/awesome-selfhosted","categoryHTML":"<h2>Money, Budgeting and Management</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://inventree.readthedocs.io/en/latest/\">Inventree</a> - InvenTree is an open-source inventory management system which provides intuitive parts management and stock control. (<a href=\"https://github.com/inventree/InvenTree\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/inventree/InvenTree\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">313</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":313,\"repo\":\"inventree/InvenTree\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->) <code>MIT</code> <code>Python</code></li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:33:34.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"cristianoliveira/awesome4girls","categoryHTML":"<h2>General</h2><h3>Conferences/Talks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://ghc.anitab.org/\">Grace Hopper Celebration of Women in Computing</a></p>\n<p>The Grace Hopper Celebration of Women in Computing is the world's largest gathering of women technologists. It is produced by the Anita Borg Institute and presented in partnership with ACM.</p>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-03-10T19:27:52.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"aniftyco/awesome-tailwindcss","categoryHTML":"<h2>UI Libraries, Components &#x26; Templates</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>🧩 <a href=\"https://github.com/kenhyuwa/litepie-datepicker\">Litepie Date picker</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/kenhyuwa/litepie-datepicker\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;fon